sections.text: Terms, defined.For purposes of the Primary Care Investment Act:(1) Department means the Department of Insurance; and(2) Primary care physician means a physician licensed under the Uniform Credentialing Act and practicing in the area of family medicine, pediatrics, internal medicine, geriatrics, obstetrics and gynecology, or general medicine.SourceLaws 2022, LB863, ยง 13.Cross ReferencesUniform Credentialing Act, see section 38-101.
